{
  "text": "p14 regulates late endosomal ERK activation and the delivery of Salmonella to LAMP1-and NADPH-oxidasepositive compartments Previous studies have revealed that ERK signaling plays an important role at several phases during Salmonella infection. On the one hand, host cells activate ERK through Toll-like receptors upon infection [CITATION_1] , and ERK signaling triggers the production of several pro-inflammatory mediators [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . On the other hand, Salmonella expresses effector proteins to subvert ERK-mediated signaling [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Therefore, we wanted to investigate whether p14 regulates ERK activation in macrophages upon Salmonella infection, and whether p14 interferes with the transport of Salmonella to late endosomal compartments.",
  "correct_citation": {
